(27, 'Honey.<br/>thank you for buying this wonderful gift for me.<br/>No.<br/>You never never remember my birthday.<br/>Oh it\'s from Stanley and Emily.<br/>Stanley  Emily.<br/>thank you so much for this wonderful gift.<br/>you are welcome.<br/>Happy birthday mom.<br/>I have never expected you.<br/>to give me such wonderful chocolate.<br/>Next Sunday.<br/>I will take you out to go shopping together.<br/>Wow  thank you mom.<br/>I will buy a new skirt for you.<br/>Stanley  we are friends now.<br/>I won\'t be a tiger mother again.<br/>Great.<br/>Can I play computer games for a while.<br/>Not after you do your homework.<br/>Fine  just keep it.<br/>Okay  have chocolate with it.<br/>A tiger mother is.<br/>very strict with her child.<br/>in order to foster.<br/>an academically competitive spirit.<br/>This form of upbringing is intended to direct.<br/>a child towards financially successful careers.<br/>at the potential risk of.<br/>feeling emotionally unfulfilled.<br/>Honey.<br/>In this conversation.<br/>we use honey to refer to.<br/>one\'s husband/wife or girlfriend.<br/>or a child in the family.<br/>Honey is a name that you call.<br/>someone you love much.<br/>Honey why so late today.<br/>You look so tired and unhappy.<br/>What happened.<br/>I`ve felt upset for the whole day.<br/>Why  what happened.<br/>We had an English dictation.<br/>I was so disappointed.<br/>that I couldn`t spell a couple of words I know.<br/>English is your favorite subject.<br/>you have never had any problems.<br/>Yes  I didn`t do well in math.<br/>and since then I spent hours and hours.<br/>practicing math exercises.<br/>Now I am doing ok in math.<br/>but my English is lagging behind.<br/>OK Don`t worry.<br/>Since you know where you can improve.<br/>what you need to do is to work at it.<br/>You know don`t take one or two low grades so seriously.<br/>So if you know what you can improve.<br/>you just go ahead and practice it.<br/>What makes me upset is that I quarreled with Lily today.<br/>Why  You are great friends aren`t you.<br/>Why did you quarrel with each other.<br/>This morning.<br/>we were doing some physics exercises together.<br/>I made some comments that might have hurt her.<br/>She cried and I decided to come home alone.<br/>without waiting for her.<br/>I see.<br/>I would suggest that you talk to her.<br/>and say sorry to her tomorrow.<br/>when you see her tomorrow morning  ok.<br/>You know good friends should be considerate.<br/>and also good friends need to care for each other.<br/>Sometimes I think you need to also control your feelings.<br/>I know  mum.<br/>I will apologize to her tomorrow.<br/>I hope we can work it out.<br/>Yeah I think Lily is a good girl.<br/>I think she will forget about it.<br/>when she knows that you really feel sorry about it.<br/>You are a nice mum.<br/>You always understand me.<br/>and never feel angry with me.<br/>You know.<br/>we do talk a lot and we share everything right.<br/>Hehe.<br/>I think you will be my best friend forever.<br/>Sure.', '2017-04-19'),
(29, 'A straight-A student got a C in cooking class and didn\'t like it. She didn\'t like it so much that her dad filed a complaint in federal court about it. He alleges that the teacher, who is white, discriminated against his daughter, who is black. He seeks to have her grade changed from a C to an A and asks for unspecified financial damages.<br/><br/>Virginia Brown is in the ninth grade at Ashley High School. Since her first year in school, she has had perfect attendance and all her grades have been A\'s. Virginia\'s father said her heart was broken when she got the C.<br/><br/>\"She cried the whole weekend,\" he said. \"She wouldn\'t come out of her room. Her eyes were red and puffy. My little girl hasn\'t been this upset since her cat got run over by a car when she was 6 years old.\"<br/><br/>Virginia is a model student. She\'s the class president. She\'s on the swim team, the volleyball team, and the track team. She belongs to the chess club. She is a member of the Girl Scouts and sings in her church choir.<br/><br/>The home economics teacher is 28-year-old Jessica Smith. This is her first year teaching. Ms. Smith said that discrimination was absolutely not the issue. \"Some of my best friends are African-Americans,\" she said. \"This isn\'t a black and white problem. Everybody in America wants to sue everybody else. I\'m going to sue them for defamation of character and whatever else my lawyer comes up with.\"<br/><br/>The school principal, who grew up in India, said that he supported Ms. Smith 100 percent. He said that Virginia is an excellent student who would have no problem getting into the best universities even with a C in cooking. \"She won\'t have any difficulty finding a great university, but she might have problems finding a husband,\" he laughed. \"She\'d better look for a man who likes to eat out a lot.\"', '2017-04-21'),
(33, 'Established in London in 1995, Huxley has enjoyed rapid growth to become an international recruitment consultancy, operating in Europe, North America, South America, the Middle East, Asia and Australia.<br/><br/>A trusted brand with a global ... Read more<br/>Mission: Our commitment to customer satisfaction has determined the dramatic success of our company.<br/><br/>The most successful companies are driven by the power of individuals working in unison through a set of common goals and values. Our company values were shaped when our top-performers were asked about the principles they adopt to enable them to provide clients and candidates with a first-rate service. Their feedback proved priceless in developing our values:<br/>', '2017-04-21'),
(34, 'Egencia<br/>Egencia, the business travel division of Expedia, is at the center of revolutionizing business travel with our cutting edge technology and products in the industry. We are one of the fastest growing brands within Expedia, Inc. and in our 12 year history we have grown from a small start-up to become one of the largest corporate travel management companies in the world.<br/><br/>We are seeking a Software Development Engineer to join our team! The team\'s responsibilities span web development and backend travel services as well as multiple languages: Java, JavaScript, and CSS.<br/><br/><br/>RESPONSIBILITIES:<br/>Besides technical design and development of business features and technical platforms, you are responsible for overall code quality, delivering features, investigations and resolving hotfixes to the live site, and more. In addition, our developers are involved in specification reviews, bug triage, system analysis, and performance tuning.<br/><br/><br/>QUALIFICATIONS:<br/>- 2-3 yrs of software development experience including development of highly interactive, web applications<br/><br/>- 2-3 yrs experience using Java<br/><br/>- Proven success using Java development environment (Hibernate, Spring, MVC)<br/><br/>- Proficient in programming concepts and web technologies (Java and scripting)<br/><br/>- Knowledge of SQL and the ability to read and understand data models and relational databases<br/><br/>- Demonstrated ability to understand complex technical details and build test methodologies for it<br/><br/>- Experience with front-end web technologies, including JavaScript, HTML5, CSS3<br/><br/>- Deep understanding of browser/device capabilities and limitations<br/><br/>- Experience building responsive web pages using CSS frameworks (LESS/SASS, Bootstrap, Foundation, etc.)<br/><br/>- Exposure to at least one MVC framework (e.g. Spring, Rails)<br/><br/>- Experience in Agile method, a strong plus<br/><br/>- Experience with applying Big Data technologies and techniques in an Enterprise environment, a plus<br/><br/>- Experience working with AWS products (e.g. S3, ECS, EMR), a plus<br/><br/>- Excellent problem solving and strong communication skills<br/><br/>- BA/BS degree in an Engineering discipline is preferred<br/><br/>Who are we:<br/><br/>We believe in being Different. We seek new ideas, different ways of thinking, diverse backgrounds and approaches, because averages can lie and sameness is dangerous. Because of this belief, our norms aren\'t rules or universal at all corners of our company. But they are important to our identity and how we work together. Like our company, these norms will evolve.<br/><br/>We are Transparent. We communicate openly and honestly, at all levels, upwards, sideways and downwards. We surface difficult issues quickly, we act,we learn.<br/><br/>We organize for Speed. We seek to gather data as fast as possible, and move. Speed allows us to make mistakes and constantly improve.<br/><br/>We believe in theScientific Method. Everyones ideas are equal in the face of hard data. We use data to guide but not define our actions.<br/><br/>We Lead Humbly. Our leaders serve their teams. None of us has all of the answers, but we are curious and we are always looking to learn. Though our leaders take their responsibilities to our business and their teams incredibly seriously, they never take themselves too seriously.<br/><br/>We act as One Team. We look to optimize for the greater good, not just our own, or even our own teams\' interests. We are actively interested in the success of others.<br/><br/>*LI-ES1<br/><br/>Expedia is committed to creating an inclusive work environment with a diverse workforce. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, gender, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, national origin, genetics, disability, age, or veteran status. This employer participates in E-Verify. The employer will provide the Social Security Administration (SSA) and, if necessary, the Department of Homeland Security (DHS) with information from each new employee\'s I-9 to confirm work authorization.', '2017-04-21'),
(35, 'As an edX learner, you`re part of a unique global community ` full of members in search of the best educational experiences the world has to offer. <br/><br/>We`re pleased to see that you`ve been working your way through one of our self-paced courses, which gives you the flexibility to works toward your goals at your own pace. You`ve fit quality-learning time into an already packed schedule around family, friends, and perhaps a full time job. <br/><br/>We wanted to send you a quick reminder that the course you`re taking will soon be coming to a close, and you`ll want to keep an eye on the end date, which you can find on your dashboard, and be sure to finish. <br/><br/>You`ve done so much amazing work already! Now it`s time to buckle down, sprint to the finish, and join the millions of other learners who`ve gained world-class knowledge through edX!', '2017-04-21'),
(36, 'Now that you have completed Week 1, I\'d like to take this opportunity to highlight a couple of the many wonderful comparisons of the job search process. There are so many great spoken examples on ApprenNet as well, but here are a couple of the Written Job Search comparisons that used language of compare/contrast very effectively:', '2017-04-21'),
(37, 'From a student in Cameroon: In Cameroon finding a job is not easy. The process is, in many ways similar to what happens in the United States. Both Cameroonian and American job seekers have to coplete a formal job application process that includes writing a resumÃ© and going throuhg an interview. Unlike in the United States, in Cameroon the use of social media is not dominant in advertising and apply for jobs. In Cameroon, many companies post their job offers in print news papers or send them to various radio stations to be read. Word of mouth is as important in Cameroon as in the U.S. Many people talk to their friends and relatives to get information about or recommendation for a job. Job search in the two countries is also different because in Cameroon job placement agencies play an important role. Some companies hire these agencies to recruit on their behalf. This means that the agency will send out the announcement, receive applications and interview candidates for the prospective employer. The role of job agencies is similar to that of SEM in the U.S. because both structures assist employers in finding suitable employees. But, job agencies use more traditional methods of communication whereas SEM resorts to online tools and social media platforms.', '2017-04-21'),
(38, 'From a student in Georgia: Both in the United States and my country internet plays important role in job search process. One thing my country has in common with the US is that personal recommendations play the important part in choosing the appropriate candidate for the specific position. Most of the job seekers use internet media and job opening websites to find the proper job but most effective ways for finding a job is personal relations and networking.Unlike the US in my country, social media like Facebook or LinkedIn is rarely used for the assessment of the professional skills and personal traits of the candidates. In US most of the job seekers prefer to work in private sector whereas in my country people prefer to work in public institutions, because of the high salary and better social protection.', '2017-04-21'),
(39, 'As you begin Week 2, you will be learning about the standards of a written resume. When you are asked to provide contact information, we realize that you may not want to give your REAL address, phone number, or email. In that case, please follow the standard format, but change the information to something very general like this:', '2017-04-21'),
