(69, 'Hi Xiaodong and Zheyu.<br/>LetÃ¢``s talk about relationships around the world.<br/>Sounds great.<br/>I guess they must be very different.<br/>in other countries.<br/>Actually there are not so many differences.<br/>between Chinese and Western people.<br/>when it comes to relationships.<br/>After all.<br/>everyone around the world wants the same things.<br/>a loving family and friends to have fun with.<br/>However there are some small differences.<br/>that you may notice if you meet some Western people.<br/>When you meet someone for the first time.<br/>a handshake is a polite way to introduce yourself.<br/>it is important to take a strong grip.<br/>and give a firm handshake.<br/>Westerners think that a weak grip means.<br/>that you do not have confidence.<br/>Eye contact is also very important.<br/>regardless of who youÃ¢``re talking to.<br/>Even if youÃ¢``re speaking with your boss.<br/>or your friendÃ¢``s grandmother.<br/>you should make sure to.<br/>keep eye contact with that person.<br/>If you look away too much.<br/>Westerners will think you lack confidence.<br/>and are impolite.<br/>So I should look the other people in the eye.<br/>and give him a handshake  right.<br/>ThatÃ¢``s right.<br/>Why do not we try it now.<br/>Nice to meet you.<br/>Very well done.<br/>How about my close relationships.<br/>Couples in Western countries often hug and.<br/>kiss each other and hold hands in public.<br/>but friends will never hold hands.<br/>Couples may also often say.<br/>I love you to each other.<br/>and family members will.<br/>say it to each other as well.<br/>When choosing someone to marry.<br/>the families are not important.<br/>The man and woman will decide by themselves.<br/>and may not care about what their families think.<br/>They may choose each other because of love.<br/>and not care about money or status.<br/>However this can sometimes end up in divorce.<br/>because the man and woman are not.<br/>well-suited for each other.<br/>How should I act with my frien