opposite gender.<br/>However.<br/>hugging between male friends.<br/>doesn\'t usually happen.<br/>If you are unsure.<br/>it is best to offer a friendly, firm handshake.<br/>In many European and Latin American cultures.<br/>however.<br/>kissing the cheek.<br/>is a common form of greeting.<br/>both in families and among friends.<br/>Each culture has their own rules.<br/>as how to kiss.<br/>touching cheeks.<br/>and kissing the air or lips to cheeks.<br/>when to kiss.<br/>saying hello or goodbye.<br/>only on special occasions.<br/>or who to kiss.<br/>family, friends,or new acquaintances.<br/>If you are unsure.<br/>it is best to ask a friend.<br/>or do some quick research.<br/>to find out.<br/>what is the customary way of.<br/>greeting each other in their culture.', '2017-04-24'),
