(93, 'I\'m Anant Agarwal, I\'m the president of edX,<br/>I\'m also a professor of electrical engineering and computer science<br/>at MIT.<br/>Online learning is revolutionizing the world.<br/>Education will never be the same again, and edX<br/>is at the cutting edge of this revolution,<br/>so when you take edX courses online, you are part of this evolution.<br/>Online learning is the ultimate democratizer.<br/>When you learn on edX, you\'re joining a community.<br/>Imagine taking a class with 100,000 or more students-- this social,<br/>this is a lot of fun.<br/>I think you will enjoy the experience.<br/>At edX it\'s about people, it\'s not about profit.<br/>For you, edX is about the best courses from the best schools and the best<br/>professors.<br/>Becoming a member of edX is easy.<br/>SPEAKER 2: We\'re really excited to have you here.<br/>We\'re going to get you started-- quick, three easy steps, browse,<br/>choose, and have some fun.<br/>Registration takes seconds, and once you register just browse the courses.<br/>When you find something that you like, click it.<br/>It\'s that easy.<br/>Choose wisely, you\'re selecting courses from the best schools<br/>all around the world.<br/>Make sure to check the prerequisites.<br/>Now you can choose your course and you\'re on your way.<br/>Welcome to the club.<br/>SPEAKER 3: Now that you\'ve signed up for course, you can view courseware.<br/>The courseware is made up of great videos, automated feedback,<br/>and cool interactive features, all for self-paced learning.<br/>The interactives are designed to help you<br/>explore your understanding of key concepts.<br/>A big part of edX is getting instant feedback on your answers,<br/>frequently in the form of a green check mark.<br/>In a lot of questions, you can try as many times<br/>as you need to get that right answer.<br/>Courses can be tough, we make sure that they\'re rigorous,<br/>but they can also be a lot of fun.<br/>A big part of edX is the social aspect.<br/>You can be a social as you want on the discussion boards.<br/>In our forums, there\'s an active community.<br/>It\'s not just the professors, students help each other out.<br/>A typical course can run a semester length, or about 12 weeks.<br/>At the end of that course, if you\'ve met the course requirements,<br/>you can get a certificate of mastery.<br/>Once you\'ve completed the course, you\'re part of our group of lifelong learners.<br/>ANANT AGARWAL: EdX\'s mission is to help you get a quality education.<br/>EdX will increase access to learning for students such as yourself worldwide.<br/>This is fun, this is exciting, and this is revolutionary.<br/>Welcome to edX, come join us.<br/>', '2017-04-27'),
(94, 'In the first section<br/>we discussed different<br/>kinds of food from different countries<br/>What people prefer to eat varies widely<br/>between countries<br/>In the text<br/>we learned about the eating habits<br/>and preferences of Thais  Koreans<br/>Japanese  Italians  British<br/>and also the Chinese<br/>Next  let`s listen to a few students<br/>from different countries<br/>to talk about their own favorite food<br/>Hey Madison<br/>who are you waiting for<br/>Oh  I\'m not waiting for anybody<br/>I\'m just trying to<br/>decide what I want to for lunch<br/>You know some friends<br/>and I are going to<br/>a Korean restaurant<br/>Would you like to join us<br/>I\'m sure you are going to<br/>have some traditional Korean food<br/>Well  I don\'t really like<br/>spicy food very much<br/>Not all the dishes are spicy<br/>They have for example<br/>Zicaibaofan  and<br/>they have Dajiang Tang<br/>I am sure you will like them<br/>Well  thanks for inviting me<br/>but I\'d rather not bother you<br/>Well  we can have lunch<br/>another time then', '2017-04-27'),
(95, 'Ok<br/>I am really hungry<br/>I really want to<br/>have a pizza right now<br/>I don\'t really like pizza<br/>It\'s too greasy for me<br/>Really  I\'m crazy about pizza<br/>Well  I\'ll have something<br/>different today<br/>Ok  well  in that case<br/>I will go to Zijing cafeteria<br/>and have a pizza<br/>So see you later<br/>Bye  enjoy your pizza<br/>Oh hey  Madison<br/>What are you doing here<br/>Well  I\'m trying to decide<br/>what I want for lunch<br/>Ok  what do you normally<br/>have for lunch at home<br/>Well  I usually have<br/>sandwiches or hamburgers<br/>But my favorite are hotdogs<br/>Well  we don\'t have<br/>too many junk foods in China<br/>but we have a lot of Chinese food<br/>But it\'s very<br/>nutritious and delicious<br/>Well  do you have any suggestions<br/>because there are so many<br/>different kinds of Chinese food<br/>Well  I\'m going to have<br/>rice noodles with beef<br/>Would you like to try it<br/>What is that<br/>Well  the noodles<br/>are made with rice<br/>and the beef is boiled and added<br/>into the soup and noodles<br/>It\'s really tasty<br/>and it\'s very popular<br/>in the South of China<br/>like Guangdong province<br/>That sounds great<br/>I\'ve never had that dish before<br/>Ok  Well should we go to<br/>the Cafeteria now and try it<br/>Sure<br/>So how are you<br/>enjoying living in China<br/>I really love it<br/>especially the Chinese culture<br/>Ok  how are you<br/>enjoying the food<br/>I don\'t really know much about it<br/>because there is<br/>such a wide variety<br/>What sort of foods do you like<br/>Maybe I can recommend you<br/>some Chinese food<br/>Well  I really like chicken and beef<br/>But I can\'t eat a lot of<br/>spicy food like hotpot<br/>Ok  maybe you\'d like foods<br/>from Shanghai or Guangzhou Province<br/>They\'re quite light<br/>not too spicy<br/>tasty and very healthy<br/>That sounds really nice<br/>At home<br/>we have a lot of junk food<br/>so I\'d really like to try that<br/>Ok  well I hope you<br/>enjoy trying it<br/>and the rest of your experience<br/>in China', '2017-04-27'),
(96, 'I\'m sure I will<br/>Thanks for the advice<br/>Guys  can you believe it<br/>It has been a month here<br/>and I really miss home<br/>Yeah I am looking at<br/>all these pictures of Melbourne<br/>I really miss home too<br/>Yeah actually what is Melbourne like<br/>Melbourne  well<br/>for one<br/>coffee is really good<br/>What is the food culture like there<br/>Well  we have barbecues a lot<br/>so I guess every weekend<br/>it would be a tradition<br/>for most families to<br/>have a barbecue<br/>out in the back yard<br/>Usually<br/>lots of sausages<br/>meat pies<br/>It`s very quintessential Australian<br/>And of course<br/>as I was mentioning about the coffee<br/>we drink a lot of coffee<br/>Have you ever tried<br/>kangaroo burgers<br/>No  I actually haven`t<br/>I don`t think<br/>that`s a pretty big thing<br/>in Australia<br/>We have normal beef burgers<br/>Oh  that`s a shame<br/>I thought you were<br/>all barbarians down under<br/>No  Angus beef is<br/>really popular<br/>and actually Hungry Jack`s<br/>which is a fast food chain store<br/>they have angus beef burgers<br/>especially for Australia<br/>What are the beaches like<br/>in Australia<br/>Well  the beaches<br/>Bondi beach in Sydney<br/>is very famous<br/>I remember<br/>a couple of years back<br/>Paris Hilton went to Bondi beach<br/>during her Australian trip<br/>It`s just in the summer<br/>there are lots and lots of people<br/>It`s completely packed<br/>And yeah  beaches are<br/>an integral part of<br/>Australian culture<br/>I mean  you have your barbecues<br/>and then you have your beaches<br/>Have you ever been to<br/>Gold Coast<br/>Well', '2017-04-27'),
(97, 'I`ve actually never been to<br/>the Gold Coast<br/>But I`d really like to go<br/>They do have<br/>a lot of adventure parks<br/>over there<br/>Like Dream World<br/>Water World<br/>So that would be nice<br/>My impression of Australia is<br/>in general<br/>is that they`re very laid back<br/>Is that a stereotype<br/>or is that true<br/>That is extremely true<br/>I think we are some of<br/>the most laid-back people<br/>in the world<br/>I mean that is just an assumption<br/>But if you come to Australia<br/>and  I think you have  haven`t you<br/>Yeah  I`ve actually been to<br/>Sydney and Brisbane<br/>I really enjoyed my trips<br/>Yeah  what did you<br/>think about the people<br/>Yeah  I thought<br/>basically<br/>I stayed with<br/>a host family in Brisbane<br/>It was a really nice house<br/>by the coast<br/>and I just thought that Australians<br/>in general<br/>are just really friendly<br/>personable<br/>and yeah I am a big fan<br/>But I think<br/>I`d really like to go one day<br/>Yeah  that would be great<br/>I will show you around<br/>Great<br/>In this section<br/>we listen to several dialogues<br/>that give us information about<br/>the foods of other countries<br/>and about English words<br/>that are used to describe food<br/>Some of the words and phrases<br/>introduced in this section are<br/> crazy about<br/>When someone says<br/>they are  crazy about  something<br/>it means they really<br/>really like it<br/>You can be  crazy about<br/>food  sports  music<br/>or just about anything<br/>Another expression is<br/> sweet tooth<br/>Having a  sweet tooth<br/>means that person really<br/>loves sugary food<br/>like candy and cake<br/> heavy food<br/>This kind of food<br/>makes your stomach<br/>feel heavy after you eat<br/>It could be oily<br/>or greasy food like fried food<br/>creamy food<br/>or have lots of meat<br/>especially beef<br/> fussy eater<br/>Another word for  fussy eater<br/>is  picky eater<br/>A fussy  or picky eater<br/>is someone who<br/>carefully chooses their food<br/>and they will only eat certain things<br/>and rarely tries to eat anything new<br/>They pick certain things<br/>to eat and refuse to<br/>eat anything else<br/>For example<br/>children are often picky/fussy eaters', '2017-04-27'),
(98, '<br/><br/><br/><br/>The opposite would be<br/>an adventurous eater<br/>which is somebody<br/>who will try anything<br/>Here are some words and phrases<br/>that are not in the dialogue<br/>but will also be helpful to know<br/> slurp<br/>this words describes<br/>the loud sucking sound<br/>that is sometimes made<br/>when one eats soup or foods<br/>that have a lot of liquid<br/>In some parts of the world<br/>this sound is not impolite to make<br/>but in many Western countries<br/>including America and England<br/>this sound is very rude<br/>to make while eating<br/>It is generally considered polite<br/>to eat as quietly as possible<br/>Bland food is food<br/>that doesn`t have very much flavor<br/>Sometimes to make food<br/>taste less bland<br/>people will add salt<br/>or try to make it spicy<br/>Rice is a bland food<br/>However  if you fry the rice<br/>then add some vegetables<br/>and some meat<br/>it becomes quite flavorful<br/>and is no longer bland<br/>From the previous conversations<br/>have you learned<br/>some English expressions<br/>about inviting people<br/>to dinner<br/>or discussing food<br/>you like and dislike<br/>Now<br/>let`s summarize the expressions<br/>that we can use to talk about<br/>food and eating habits<br/>OK  now<br/>The following are expressions<br/>you can use<br/>while talking about<br/>your habits<br/>or your tastes for food<br/>You may also practice<br/>using them in your daily life<br/>Talking about food you like<br/>when talking about food you like<br/>you may use<br/>the following expressions<br/>or the following sentences<br/>or patterns<br/>My favorite food is<br/>smoked salmon<br/>I like it the best<br/>Sentence 2<br/>I`m crazy about Mexican food<br/>3<br/>I like cakes  cookies and ice cream<br/>I really have a sweet tooth<br/>4<br/>I always eat heavy food<br/>5<br/>The smell of barbecued chicken<br/>usually makes my mouth water<br/>6<br/>I can eat any kind of food<br/>When Talking about food you dislike<br/>you may say<br/>I can`t stand fish  vegetables<br/>or eggs<br/>I`m a fussy eater<br/>I don`t like this soda<br/>It tastes too sweet<br/>I can`t stand greasy food<br/>I don`t like salty food very much', '2017-04-27'),
